                  <summary><p>Paper manuscript from the GOML [R.5734/TR.1050]. Poems continuously written on both sides, separated by several lines, brittle and now laminated. Donated by the Bhavanandam Academy in 1955/56. Complete (apart from AN 336–343), misnumbered from 107 onwards, with traditional colophon (p. 262f.), followed by the beginning of a name index in a different hand, followed by another AN KV–5 in a different hand (less neat).</p>
<p>Poems are divided into lines, but lines are not split into metrical feet, sandhi is upon the whole preserved, though there are deviations. Individual poems followed by their kiḷavi(-s), author's name and European number.</p>
<p>Closely agreeing with other mss, i.e. TT, NL, C1, C5, C6, G2 and sharing a number of new mistakes and lacunae with C9 and G2; possibly a copy of C9 before correction and adding a number of individual mistakes and corrections.</p></summary>
                  
